properties.areaDesc: Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 29 at 2:14PM MST until March 2 at 5:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...MODERATE TO HEAVY SNOW AT TIMES WILL IMPACT AREAS ALONG AND
WEST OF THE LARAMIE RANGE SUNDAY THROUGH MONDAY MORNING...

* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 3 to 6
inches. East winds may gust up to 30 mph at times.

* WHERE...Southwest Platte County and the central Laramie Range.

* WHEN...From 11 AM Sunday to 5 AM MST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Transportation may be impacted with snow covered
roads...drifting snow and poor visibility. Plan on slippery road
conditions.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 11 AM SUNDAY TO 5 AM MST MONDAY
